<refentry id="bif.Filter" xreflabel="Filter">

<refmeta>
<indexterm>
<primary>Filter</primary>
</indexterm>

<refentrytitle>Filter</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>Built-in function</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>Filter</refname>
<refpurpose>
Filters a list based on a criterion
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis>
Filter[x->NLIST(T*), y->NLIST(BOOLEAN)] =: LIST(T)
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>
<function>Filter</function> returns a list with the same dimension structure 
as <parameter>list</parameter>, with the
elements for which the corresponding elements of <parameter>by</parameter> are
<literal>False</literal>
removed.  It is an error if <parameter>x</parameter> and <parameter>y</parameter> do not have the same
dimensionality.
</para>
</refsect1>

